abstract: Doctors suspected infection with the virus, but the patient did not fit the federal criteria and was not tested for days.
snippet: Doctors suspected infection with the virus, but the patient did not fit the federal criteria and was not tested for days.
lead_paragraph: Already in deep distress, the patient was rushed last week to a hospital in Northern California, severely ill and unable to breathe on her own.

abstract: United Nations human rights chief Michelle Bachelet said on Thursday U.S. President Donald Trump's administration was endangering public health and the rights of children with its policies on the environment and migration.
snippet: United Nations human rights chief Michelle Bachelet said on Thursday U.S. President Donald Trump's administration was endangering public health and the rights of children with its policies on the environment and migration.
lead_paragraph: GENEVA — United Nations human rights chief Michelle Bachelet said on Thursday U.S. President Donald Trump's administration was endangering public health and the rights of children with its policies on the environment and migration.
headline_main: U.N. Rights Chief Rips Trump Policies on Environment, Migration
headline_print_headline: U.N. Rights Chief Rips Trump Policies on Environment, Migration

abstract: The Court of Appeal said the government failed to take its climate change commitments into account, a decision that carries global implications
snippet: The Court of Appeal said the government failed to take its climate change commitments into account, a decision that carries global implications
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain’s Court of Appeal issued a landmark ruling on Thursday that stymied plans to build a third runway at Heathrow Airport in London, declaring that the government illegally neglected its commitments to reduce carbon emissions and protect the planet from dangerously high temperatures.

abstract: Democratic presidential hopefuls spread out across South Carolina on Thursday as the clock ticked down to the state's Saturday primary, the first big test of their appeal with African-American voters.

lead_paragraph: MCCLELLANVILLE, S.C/WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. — Democratic presidential hopefuls spread out across South Carolina on Thursday as the clock ticked down to the state's Saturday primary, the first big test of their appeal with African-American voters.

abstract: Republican activists in South Carolina are urging party voters to do the seemingly unthinkable: support U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders' bid for the White House in the state's Democratic primary on Saturday.

lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Republican activists in South Carolina are urging party voters to do the seemingly unthinkable: support U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders' bid for the White House in the state's Democratic primary on Saturday.

abstract: Did the police fail to act as the country descended into its worst spasm of religious violence in years? Witnesses say officers stood by when Hindu mobs attacked Muslims.
snippet: Did the police fail to act as the country descended into its worst spasm of religious violence in years? Witnesses say officers stood by when Hindu mobs attacked Muslims.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — The mob smashed through the gate and cut the electricity. The men stormed up the steps, chanting the name of a Hindu god and brandishing knives, chains, iron bars and pieces of pipe.
